!! Quickest possible

```
<$mindmap filter="[tag[Knowledge]]" engine="MindElixir" overlay="$:/state/example/overlay" height="500"/>
```

The widget creates the overlay tiddler on first user gesture. Reload — the layout persists.

!! Knowledge-app — single area, drag-friendly

View tiddler `Demo/llm-mindmap`:

```
mm.producer:  knowledge-tree
mm.args:      {"area":"llm"}
mm.engine:    MindElixir
mm.options:   {"direction":2, "draggable":true}
mm.overlay:   $:/state/rimir/mindmap/views/demo-llm/overlay
```

Render:

```
<$mindmap view="Demo/llm-mindmap" height="600"/>
```

!! Without the toolbar / context menu

For embedding in a small panel:

```
mm.options:   {"toolBar":false, "contextMenu":false, "keypress":false}
```

!! Verification (browser)

# Install `rimir/mindmap` and `rimir/mindmap-elixir`. Restart.
# Create the view tiddler above (or substitute another area id).
# Open a tiddler containing `<$mindmap view="Demo/llm-mindmap" height="600"/>`.
# A radial mindmap should render. The toolbar shows ``producer: knowledge-tree`` and ``engine: MindElixir``.
# Drag a node onto a new parent. The overlay tiddler appears at `$:/state/rimir/mindmap/views/demo-llm/overlay` with an `op: "reparent"` entry.
# Reload the wiki. The layout persists (read from the overlay on render).

